arch:property.oc:show_val: Moderate size, midden-type density. Mostly sheep-size, some large mammal. Good surface condition (weathering stage 2/3). Moderate fragmentation with some large pieces. Taxa include horse, sheep, goat, and pig. Moderate levels of gnawing and digestion. Few cut-marks. Appears to be midden similar to 8869, with fewer cut-marks. Fish and bird also present. Body part distribution is well-balanced. F1, F2, and F3 are bone points. The surfaces of five bone fragments were polished and appeared worn rather than weathered, possibly due to water-rolling/trampling. One cow skull fragment exhibited mixed high temperature burning, indicated by both green and gray coloring. Flotation Sample #1, 4mm 100% sorted, only diagnostics recorded, rest as flot frags. Flotation sample material was similar to dry sieved material. Distribution of taxa was also similar to that of dry-sieve. While sheep and goat (primarily sheep) predominate in the flotation sample, horse, cattle, pig-size, medium carnivore, bird, and microfauna were also present. Substantial modern breakage was observed, in particular, a sheep/goat right frontal (right half of forehead and upper eye socket) was partially reconstructed from approximately 7-8 fragments, all modern fractures. Last Number=F837

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
